cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "dopa: a local-first, dopamine-aware ADHD assistant for heavy AI-tool users"
message: "If you use dopa in your work or research, please cite it."
type: software
authors:
  - name: "PDAC Research Labs"
repository-code: "https://github.com/PDACResearchLabs/dopa"
abstract: >-
  dopa is a two-layer ADHD-support tool: a Claude Code skill for interactive
  diagnosis and check-ins, plus a local-first passive sensor daemon that detects
  hyperfocus, avoidance, fatigue, and crash patterns from on-device signals
  (and, opt-in, cloud webcam-affect analysis). It was built to help people whose
  ADHD symptoms intensify under heavy AI-coding-agent use.
keywords:
  - ADHD
  - human-AI interaction
  - developer wellbeing
  - hyperfocus
  - dopamine
license: MIT
version: 0.1.0
date-released: "2026-06-15"
